India's Central Bank Raises Inflation Forecast to 7% From 6%

-- B y   K a r t i k   G o y a l
-- 
2011-07-26T05:28:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/india-s-central-bank-raises-inflation-forecast-to-7-from-6-.html
India 's central bank raised its
inflation forecast for the year ending March 31 to 7 percent from
6 percent citing higher fuel and food prices.  The Reserve Bank of India said it's ``desirable'' to raise
fuel costs even as inflation accelerates should crude oil prices
not fall. The central bank kept its economic growth forecast for
the year at 8 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kartik Goyal in  New Delhi  at 
 kgoyal@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephanie Phang at   sphang@bloomberg.net  